INSERT INTO VIEW_TEMPLATE (VWT_OID, VWT_OWNER_OID, VWT_OWNER_TYPE, VWT_DDX_OID, VWT_NAME, VWT_CONTEXT, VWT_VIEW_DEFINITION, VWT_CUSTOM_IND, VWT_HIDE_IND, VWT_DESCRIPTION, VWT_HELP_ENABLED, VWT_PROCEDURE_ID, VWT_SCHOOL_VISIBILITY_TYPE, VWT_ROLE_VISIBILITY_TYPE, VWT_LAST_MODIFIED) VALUES ('vwtILDlmAccess', '*dst', 1, NULL, 'DLM Accessibility Features/Accomodations Form', 'form.sped-il-Dlm-Access', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <!-- #TEMPLATE-ID [form.sped-il-Dlm-Access] --> <template> <tab name=""> <row> <block> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Dynamic Learning Maps Accessibility Features/Accommodations Form Instructions</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Dynamic Learning Maps Accessibility Features/Accommodations instructions is provided to assist in identifying and documenting the accessibility features and/or accommodations for students determined eligible to take the Dynamic Learning Map (DLM) assessment. DLM is guided by the core beliefs that all students should have access to challenging, grade-level content and that educators will observe professional protocols in providing instruction and administering assessments based on this challenging content.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Accessibility features and accommodations should be chosen on the basis of the individual student''s needs, not on the basis of the disability category, grade level, or instructional setting. Accessibility features and accommodations identified for students taking the DLM are provided to ensure that the assessment will provide an accurate picture of what the student knows. It is important that as part of the IEP process, the team discusses with the parent the accessibility features and accommodations that their child will have available to them to complete the assessment. The DLM Personal Needs Profile Form will help to guide IEP teams in identifying and documenting the appropriate accessibility features and/or accommodations for students taking the DLM. Accessibility features and accommodations must be listed under each applicable test on the IEP. If the IEP team identifies accessibility features and/or accommodations to use, the Dynamic Learning Map Accessibility Features/Accommodations Form must be attached to the IEP.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Accessibility Features</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">There are two categories of accessibility features with multiple aspects. If one or more aspect of an accessibility feature is identified as appropriate, the team should record the accessibility feature on the DLM Accessibility Features/Accommodations Form and attach the form to the IEP.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">As an example, the IEP team may identify that a student who is eligible for the DLM requires magnification of the screen during testing. For this reason, magnification should be marked if it is for ELA and/or math. It is necessary to indicate if magnification will be used, but it is not necessary to identify the level of magnification. During actual testing, the level of magnification may be adjusted between "testlets" to find the most appropriate level for the student and so should not be restricted on the IEP. The option is available for districts to use the DLM system prior to the assessment administration to familiarize students with the accessibility features and/or accommodations that are available.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Accommodations</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Category three lists out specific accommodations (human read aloud, signed interpretation of text, language translation of test for math only, test administrator enters response for student, and partner-assisted scanning) that are defined by the DLM. Should any of these be identified by the IEP team as appropriate, they should be checked on the DLM Accessibility Features/Accommodations Form. Should the student require other "team-defined" accommodations not listed here but regularly used in classroom assessments, they should be listed specifically under the "team defined" box. The "team defined" accommodation should be an accommodation that does not negate the purpose of the assessment and should be familiar to the student.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">As an example, the IEP team may identify that a student who is eligible for the DLM requires a signed interpretation of the text using American Sign Language and requires the use of a stress ball. "Signed Interpretation of Text" and "Stress Ball" should be documented on the form.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">DLM Accessibility Features/Accommodations Form</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="left" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Accessibility Features</text> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Category 1: Support provided within KITE via the PNP Profile</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Magnification</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Allows screen magnification during testing. The magnification options are 2x, 3x, 4x, 5x.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-magnification" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Overlay Color</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">The overlay color is the background color of the test; the default color is white. During testing there are other alternate colors options: blue, green, pink, gray, and yellow. The font will remain black.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-overaly-color" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Invert Color Choice</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">The invert color will cause the test background to appear black with white/gray lettering. Use with "contrast color" to change the display to a different color scheme.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-invert-color" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Color Contrast</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">The contrast color section provides several background and lettering color schemes: white background with green font, white background with red font, black background with gray font, black background with yellow font.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-color-contrast" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" cell-span="1" line-span="3"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Synthetic Spoken Audio(read aloud with highlighting)</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Text Only. Provides audio for the text and not for images</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-ssa-text-only" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Text and Graphics. Provides audio for the text and an audio description of the images</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-ssa-text-graphics" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">NonVisual. Provides audio for the text, an audio description of the images, and an audio description of the layout</text> </cell> <cell align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c1-ssa-text-non-visual" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Category 2: Support Requires Additional Tools/Materials</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Uncontracted Braille</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Uncontracted (only available option)</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c2-uncontracted-braille" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Single Switch System</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Is activated using a switch set up to simulate the "Enter" key on the keyboard. On the PNP, educators can set scan speed, indicate whether scanning should begin automatically when the page appears, and select the number of times the scan cycle repeats before stopping.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c2-single-swift-system" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Two-Switch System</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Does not require activation in the PNP. Is used to emulate the tab key to move between choices, and the Enter key to select the choice when highlighted.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c2-two-switch-system" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Individualized Manipulatives</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Manipulatives that is familiar to the students to use while testing (i.e. unit cubes, interlocking blocks, counters, etc.)</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c2-individualized-manipul" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" cell-span="1" line-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Calculator</text> </cell> <cell align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Permitted to use on math testlets unless it interferes with the construct of the testlet. The Test Information Page (TIP) for each math testlet will specify whether or not a calculator is permitted.</text> </cell> <cell align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c2-calculator" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="left" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Accommodations</text> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Category 3: Support provided by the Test Administrator Outside the DLM System.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Human Read Aloud</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">If the student does not respond well to the synthetic voice, the test administrator may read the assessment to the student.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-human-read-aloud" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Signed interpretation of text</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Signing is not provided via the computer. For students who sign, test administrators may sign the content to the student using American Sign Language (ASL), Exact English, or a personalized sign system.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-signied-interpret-txt" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Language Translation of Text (Math only)</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Test administrators may translate the text for students who are English Language learners or respond best to a language other than English on the math assessment only.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-language-transl-txt" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Test administrator enters responses for student</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">If a student is unable to independently and accurately record his/her own responses into the system, the student may indicate the selected responses through normal response types and/or forms of communication such as eye gaze and the test administrator will keys in the student''s response.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-enters-responses-std" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1" line-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Partner-Assisted Scanning</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">A strategy in which test administrators assist students with scanning, or going through, students'' answer choices. Test administrators read and/or point to each answer choice and the students indicate when their desired choice is presented.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-partner-assisted-scann" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1" line-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Team-defined</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">Any accommodations that are not addressed may be implemented IF the accommodation does not negate the purpose of the assessment. Any accommodation used during testing should be familiar to the student through previous use in the student''s instructional program.</text> </cell> <cell border="bottom" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-team-defined" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="none" align="left" cell-span="1"> <text bold="true" font-size="medium">List the team defined accommodations below:</text> </cell> </line> <line align="center" shaded="true"> <cell border="none" align="left" cell-span="1"> <property alias="dlma-c3-team-defined-accomod" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> </block> </row> </tab> </template>', '0', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, 0, 0, NULL);

INSERT INTO VIEW_TEMPLATE (VWT_OID, VWT_OWNER_OID, VWT_OWNER_TYPE, VWT_DDX_OID, VWT_NAME, VWT_CONTEXT, VWT_VIEW_DEFINITION, VWT_CUSTOM_IND, VWT_HIDE_IND, VWT_DESCRIPTION, VWT_HELP_ENABLED, VWT_PROCEDURE_ID, VWT_SCHOOL_VISIBILITY_TYPE, VWT_ROLE_VISIBILITY_TYPE, VWT_LAST_MODIFIED) VALUES ('vwtILDlmPGuid', '*dst', 1, NULL, 'DLM Alternative Assessment Participation Guidance', 'form.sped-il-Dlm-P-Guid', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <!-- #TEMPLATE-ID [form.sped-il-Dlm-P-Guid] --> <template> <tab name=""> <row> <block> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">ILLINOIS STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION</text> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Dynamic Learning Maps Alternate Assessment Participation Guidance</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Students must participate in the state assessment through one of the following:</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">- the regular state assessment for the student''s grade, without accommodations,</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">- the regular state assessment for the student''s grade, with accommodations, or</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">- the alternate state assessment for the student''s grade.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Who is eligible to take the DLM Alternate Assessment?</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">The alternate assessment is intended for students with the most significant cognitive disabilities. These students have intellectual functioning well below average (typically associated with an IQ below 55) that exists concurrently with impairments or deficits in adaptive functioning (i.e. communications, self-care, home living, social/interpersonal skills, use of community resources, self-directions, functional academic skills, work leisure, health and safety). The reference to "typically associated with an IQ of below 55" is to help distinguish between students with cognitive disabilities and significant cognitive disabilities from students with the most significant cognitive disabilities. This means that many students with cognitive disabilities will not qualify for the DLM Alternate Assessment. By default, they must take our regular state assessment with or without accommodations. The inclusion of the words "typically associated with" allows for some district/school flexibility. It is by no means an absolute requirement.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Students taking the alternate assessment may be identified under a variety of educational categories, including cognitive disabilities (mental retardation), autism, multiple disabilities, and traumatic brain injury.</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Who is not eligible for consideration to take the DLM Alternate Assessment?</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Students who strictly have academic, language, social/emotional, physical or sensory disabilities without co-occurring intellectual functioning well below average.</text> </line> </block> </row> <row> <block> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">ILLINOIS STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION</text> </line> <line align="center" border="bottom" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" font-size="large">Dynamic Learning Maps Participation Guidelines</text> </line> <line align="left" border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="center" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Participation Criteria</text> </cell> <cell align="center" border="left" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Participation Criteria Descriptors</text> </cell> <cell border="left" cell-span="1" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Yes/No</text> </cell> <cell border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="true">Reason(S) for Yes or No Response</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="2" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">1. The student has a significant cognitive disability.</text> </cell> <cell align="left" border="left" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Review of student records indicate a disability or multiple disabilities that significantly impact intellectual functioning and adaptive behavior.</text> </cell> <cell border="left,bottom" cell-span="1" line-span="2" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-has-cognitive-dsblty" label-display="none" /> </cell> <cell border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="2" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-reason-for-cogn-dsblty" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true">
<cell align="left" border="left,bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" italic="true">*Adaptive behavior is defined as essential for someone to live independently and to function safely in daily life.</text> </cell>
</line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">2. The student''s instruction is linked to grade level content and reflective of the Common Core Essential Elements.</text> </cell> <cell align="left" border="left,bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">Goals and instruction listed in the IEP for this student are linked to the enrolled grade level Common Core Essential Elements and address knowledge and skills that are appropriate and challenging for this student.</text> </cell> <cell border="left,bottom" cell-span="1" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-linked-to-grade-lvl" label-display="none" /> </cell> <cell border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-reason-fro-link-gr-lvl" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="3" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">3. The student requires extensive direct individualized instruction and substantial supports to achieve measureable gains in the grade-and age-appropriate curriculum.</text> </cell> <cell align="left" border="left" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false">The student:</text> </cell> <cell border="left,bottom" cell-span="1" line-span="3" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-requires-supports" label-display="none" /> </cell> <cell border="bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="3" shaded="true"> <property alias="dmlpg-reason-fro-requires-supp" label-display="none" /> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="left" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false"> a. requires extensive, repeated, individualized instruction and support that is not of a temporary or transient nature and</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="left,bottom" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >b. uses substantially adapted materials and individualized methods of accessing information in alternative ways to acquire, maintain, generalize, demonstrate and transfer skills across multiple settings.</text> </cell> </line>
<line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="true" >IMPORTANT NOTE: </text> <text bold="false" >The IEP team''s decision that a student will take the DLM cannot be based on the following factors; however, the existence of one or more of these factors does not prevent a student from taking the DLM if they meet the other participation criteria:</text> </cell> </line>
<line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student''s achievement is significantly below that of same-age peers, even when compared to other students with disabilities.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student has an IEP.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student has a certain special education eligibility label or receives certain services.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student has excessive or extensive absences.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student has social, cultural, or economic differences.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student has English Language Learner (ELL) status.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <cell align="left" border="none" cell-span="10" line-span="1" shaded="true"> <text bold="false" >- The student may not perform well on the regular assessment, which may affect the Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP) status of the student''s home school and/or district.</text> </cell> </line> </block> </row> </tab> </template>', '0', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
